               <msContents>
                  <summary>A mid 17th-century copy of an Ottoman Turkish commentary by Kosovar author <persName xml:lang="tu" key="person_39160012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/39160012/" type="standard" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">Prizrenli Şemi Şemullah (fl. 16th c.)</persName> on the Persian <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Pandnāmah</title> (Book of Advice) spuriously ascribed to <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" key="person_120724759" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759/" role="aut" change="#role-assignment #ids-cleanup">ʻAṭṭār</persName>. 
                     In his introduction, the author states how he composed the work at the request of his friend ʿÖmer b. Ḥüseyn, which he dedicated it to the latter’s patron Zeyrek Aġa then when completed, presented it to
                     Sultan Murād III (ruled 982/1574–1003/1595). The commentary itself consists of a verse by verse quotation with translations and occasional glosses on the original
                     text.
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_889-item1">
                     <author key="person_120724759" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759/" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">ʻAṭṭār, Farīd al-Dīn, -approximately 1230</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">‏عطار، فريد الدين محمد بن ابراهيم نيشابورى‏</persName>
                     </author>
                     <author role="cmm" key="person_39160012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/39160012/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">Şemi Şemullah, Prizrenli, active 16th century</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">Shim‘ī Sham‘ Allāh</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">Sham‘ī Sham‘ Allāh</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">شمعي شمع الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="scr" key="person_f7845">
                        <persName role="scr" xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Aḥmed bin Ḳadır al-Bulevī</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="tu">Ahmet Kadır Bülevi</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ota">احمد قادر بولوى</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6859">Pandnāmah ma‘a sharḥ-i Sham‘ī</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ota" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus>
                     شکر و سپاس بی قیاس شول قادر قیومه که لطفی بی غایت و کرم بی نهایت دن مفخر شعار نبوة دثار رسول‌لر کروردی.
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ota"><locus from="66b" to="66b"> برگ ۶۶پ (folio 66b):</locus>
                        کین نصایح را بخواند او بسی که بو نصیحت‌لری او کیمسه چون اوقپیه الحمد لله علی التمام. 
                     </explicit>
                     <colophon><locus from="66b" to="66b"> برگ ۶۶پ (folio 66b):</locus>
                     </colophon>
                     <colophon>Completed by <persName role="scr">Aḥmad bin Ḳadr al-Bulavī (Turkish: Ahmet Kadır Bülevi)</persName> in the afternoon of <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1666-07-06">3 Muḥarram 1077 AH (6 Jul. 1666 CE)</date>.
                        </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>For other copies of the <title>Pandnāmah</title>, see Rylands <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7405"><idno>Persian MS 895A</idno></ref> and <idno>Gaster MS 1500B</idno>.</note>
                  </msItem>
